    "This bias is then relied upon to guide response generation; (2) The preference learning pipeline only promotes the preferred response over the non-preferred one.",
    "However, if neither response is a highly probable response to a query, this learning process would fail to deter jailbreaking behavior.",
    "Building upon these two observations, in this paper, we summarize the following two key features of attacks that are crucial to the success of jailbreak:",
    "• Query obfuscation: Removal of the statistically most easily identified constituent, e.g.",
